<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="little-adj">little <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'lɪtl/    美 /'lɪtl/  </p>
<p>[常用于名词前]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[常含感情色彩，指小得可爱] 小的；幼小的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What a pretty <strong>little girl</strong>! 
多么漂亮的小姑娘！</p></div>

<h4 id="2-less-least">2.★ <strong>(less, least) [常表否定含义，修饰不可数名词]少的；几乎没有的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There's little cooking oil left in the house. Would you go and get some?
家里没食用油了，你去买点好吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>短暂的；短距离的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let's take a rest for <strong>a little while</strong>.
我们稍微休息一会儿吧。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>琐碎的；微不足道的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There's no time to discuss every little detail.
没有时间讨论细枝末节了。</p></div>

<p>注: 形容词的比较级和最高级更常用smaller和 smallest，而littler和littlest很少见。  </p></div>